PN,46902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1777392670
OL,3,CCampaigner 'disgusted' that assisted
OL,4,Cdying bill runs out of time
OL,6,FThe Bill had proposed allowing adults
OL,7,Fin England and Wales, with fewer than
OL,8,Fsix months to live, to apply for an
OL,9,Fassisted death, subject to the
OL,10,Fapproval of two doctors and an expert
OL,11,Fpanel.
OL,13,FWhile the Bill had successfully passed
OL,14,Ftwo votes in the House of Commons,
OL,15,Falbeit with a narrower majority on the
OL,16,Fsecond occasion, it did not face a
OL,17,Fvote in the Lords.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
