PN,46903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1777392670
OL,3,CCampaigner 'disgusted' that assisted
OL,4,Cdying bill runs out of time
OL,6,FIt instead ran out of time, with Lord
OL,7,FCharlie Falconer, who had steered it
OL,8,Fthrough the upper chamber, saying he
OL,9,Ffelt "despondent" that a piece of
OL,10,Flegislation which he said was "so
OL,11,Fimportant to so many, has not failed
OL,12,Fon its merits, but failed as a result
OL,13,Fof procedural wrangling".
OL,15,FMore than 1,200 amendments to the Bill
OL,16,Fhad been suggested in the Lords, with
OL,17,Fmore than 800 of those tabled or
OL,18,Fsponsored by seven peers.
OL,26,@qD@FOUqD@QO]rD@_OUuD@XO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/8
