CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1777392670
OL,3,CCampaigner 'disgusted' that assisted
OL,4,Cdying bill runs out of time
OL,6,FTory former cabinet minister Lord
OL,7,FBaker of Dorking accused opponents of
OL,8,Fthe Bill of a "prolonged filibuster",
OL,9,Fbranding the situation a "denial of
OL,10,Fdemocracy".
OL,12,FThose opposed to the Bill have branded
OL,13,Fit "unsafe and unworkable" and "bad
OL,14,Flaw", citing their concerns around
OL,15,Fpotential coercion of vulnerable
OL,16,Fpeople and a lack of safeguards for
OL,17,Fthose with disabilities.
OL,26,@pD@OOUpD@dO]qD@ZOUrD@JO]uD@DOUuD@ZO]uD@
OL,26,A`OUvD@DO]
