PN,46907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F469A1777392670
OL,3,CCampaigner 'disgusted' that assisted
OL,4,Cdying bill runs out of time
OL,6,FSupporters have vowed to try to bring
OL,7,Fthe Bill back in Parliament's next
OL,8,Fsession, with its sponsor in the
OL,9,FCommons Kim Leadbeater, who watched
OL,10,Fproceedings from the gallery on Friday
OL,11,F` saying she will again enter her name
OL,12,Fin the ballot of private members'
OL,13,Fbills.
OL,15,FAs the draft legislation fell, Ms
OL,16,FLeadbetter stood and held her hand to
OL,17,Fher mouth, shaking her head.
OL,19,FCampaigners have said they could use
OL,20,Fthe Parliament Act to get the Bill
OL,21,Fthrough if it was selected.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/8
